descriptions["21692"]={cn:"看起来很适合你戴。",en:"Luks gud on you."};
descriptions["21693"]={cn:"是它从你脖子上长出来的，还是你从这个护身符上长出来的？",en:"Did it grow out of your neck, or was it you that grew out of this amulet?"};
descriptions["21694"]={cn:"给米希尔搜藏的鲨鱼卵。",en:"A Selachii Egg for Mishell\'s monster collection."};
descriptions["21695"]={cn:"奥铎曼为你准备了第二剂解药，能够对抗泽尼特的瘴气。",en:"Otomai has prepared your second antidote to drink, which combats the effects of Zinit Miasma."};
descriptions["21696"]={cn:"收集 100 块碎片，合成菌菇戒指。",en:"Collect 100 of these fragments to create a Kel\'Dwa."};
descriptions["21697"]={cn:"菌菇戒指看起来非常衰弱。只有奥铎麦能使其回复正常...",en:"The Kel\'Dwa seems very weak. Only Otomai can restore its former power..."};
descriptions["21699"]={cn:"给米歇尔搜藏的斯雷克卵。",en:"A Schnek Egg for Mishell\'s monster collection."};
descriptions["21700"]={cn:"把这双靴子的名字写错会让你看起来像一只真正的獾兽！",en:"Writing the name of these boots incorrectly will make you look like a real Badgerox!"};
descriptions["21701"]={cn:"传说中这双靴子能让你站在海蓝圆盾上滑行，并持弓在手而不失去准头。",en:"Legend has it that these boots allow you to surf on the Asse Shield, bow in hand, with no loss of precision."};
descriptions["21702"]={cn:"獾兽毛和仿制披风...天啊！",en:"Badgerox hair and potanicloakery... geez!"};
descriptions["21703"]={cn:"蚀影斗篷的大姐，这件披风的第一个复制品是由同一个皮匠大师设计的。",en:"Big sister of the Apothecloakery, the first copy of this cape was designed by the same leather dealer."};
descriptions["21704"]={cn:"不，装饰这个戒指的不是黑豹毛，而是獾兽毛。",en:"No, this isn\'t black panther hair decorating this ring, but Badgerox hair."};
descriptions["21705"]={cn:"獾兽的坏脾气经常让他们改变战术。像是在你砍完对手后，用这副多毛肩甲清理武器。",en:"The bad mood of Badgeroxes often makes them change their tactics. Like cleaning your weapon with these Hairpaulettes, once you\'ve finished chopping opponents."};
descriptions["21706"]={cn:"最好不要惹他们，否则事情很快就会变得很刺激...",en:"Better not mess with them, otherwise things could quickly get spicy..."};
descriptions["21707"]={cn:"相传一名从事军火事业叫“尼东·史塔克”的守护者，设计了一件能让使用者飞行的装甲，其能量由胸甲中间的红宝石提供。",en:"It\'s said that a Feca called \"Noty Strak\", who was in the business of making weapons, had the idea of creating a full set of armor that lets its wearer fly, taking its power from a ruby placed in the middle of the chest."};
descriptions["21708"]={cn:"这胸甲有一个不同寻常的特点，能够掩盖即使没有它，你也有同多的毛的事实。",en:"This breastplate has the unusual feature of hiding the fact that you\'re just as hairy even without it."};
descriptions["21709"]={cn:"粗糙的鞣制、简易的皮革，无法抵挡对手的攻击。然而，有些人享受痛苦。",en:"A clumsily tanned, simple leather, which won\'t stop your opponents\' attacks. Then again, some people enjoy the pain."};
descriptions["21710"]={cn:"以去毛后的獾兽皮制成。",en:"Armor made from Badgerox skin, from which all hair has been removed."};
descriptions["21711"]={cn:"镶嵌了獾兽尖牙的戒指，非常适合打断人的牙齿。",en:"A Badgerox Fang set into a ring, perfect for breaking people\'s teeth."};
descriptions["21712"]={cn:"也有紫红色的。",en:"Also comes in fuchsia pink."};
descriptions["21713"]={cn:"属于一名死于阿利莫堡围困中的牧民，以其爱国心及制作獾兽标本的兴趣而闻名。",en:"Slimy Rockett, who died during the siege of Fort Alimo, was a trapper who was well known for his commitments to his nation, but also for his hobby of stuffing Badgeroxes."};
descriptions["21714"]={cn:"尤其是在疲累的时候，如果你既好斗又暴力，那这顶头盔就很适合你。",en:"If you\'re aggressive and violent, especially when tired, this helmet\'s for you."};
descriptions["21715"]={cn:"你怎么会想要把这东西放在头上！？?",en:"What\'s the idea of putting this thing on your head!?"};
descriptions["21716"]={cn:"一条有着獾兽尖牙和毛的饰品。你可以自己去思考制作这条挂坠的人有多么古怪的信仰。",en:"A charm bringing together a fang and a tuft of Badgerox hair. We\'ll let you wonder what strange belief whoever made this pendant had."};
descriptions["21717"]={cn:"发酵的牛奶有着强大的治愈功能，即使只是弄在脖子附近。有让你感到惊讶吗？喝醉了才会相信这种事。",en:"Fermented Romel milk has powerful curing properties, even if it\'s only worn around the neck. Does that surprise you? It\'s got to be drunk to be believed."};
descriptions["21718"]={cn:"并非獾兽厨师在制作这件披风时没有发挥创意，而是这只是一件换下来当披风的围裙。",en:"Badgerox chefs weren\'t lacking in ingenuity when they made this cape, seeing as it\'s just an apron that\'s taken a backseat."};
descriptions["21719"]={cn:"我的披风！我的披风呢！？那不是你的！",en:"MY CAPE! WHAT ABOUT MY CAPE!? IT\'S NOT YOURS!"};
descriptions["21720"]={cn:"由柔顺的白色獾兽毛制成，总是能保持洁净。",en:"Made from silky white Badgerox hair, this cape always stays clean."};
descriptions["21721"]={cn:"以其能够准确命中弱点的能力而命名，这把双手剑效果卓越，尤其是在你的敌人对它没有提防的时候。",en:"Named for its ability to hit right where it hurts, this two-handed sword will prove to be highly effective, especially when your enemy doesn\'t suspect it."};
descriptions["21722"]={cn:"尖端非常细的匕首，使用得当还能做为缝合用...",en:"A dagger with a very fine point, which, when used properly, allows very effective sutures to be performed..."};
descriptions["21723"]={cn:"即使效果不差，这枚珠宝的装饰仍饱受争议。",en:"Although effective, the decoration of this jewel remains debatable."};
descriptions["21724"]={cn:"注意：与同名的凉鞋不同，不建议尝试把这把匕首弄在脚上走路。",en:"Be careful: unlike the sandals of the same name, it\'s inadvisable to try and walk with this dagger on your feet."};
descriptions["21725"]={cn:"皮革、牙齿以及毛发：正是这些使得猎户腰带是一条好腰带。",en:"Leather, teeth and hair: what makes the Trapper Belt great."};
descriptions["21726"]={cn:"熊獾兽家族的腰带，既不会太松也不会太紧。",en:"This belt is the model that is neither too loose nor too tight, used by the Beardger family."};
descriptions["21727"]={cn:"缝抑或不缝，这正是问题的本质所在。",en:"To knit or not to knit, that is the knitty-gritty of the question."};
descriptions["21728"]={cn:"足以把敌人弄得头下脚上。",en:"Enough to turn your enemies upside-down."};
descriptions["21729"]={cn:"把这些靴子的名字写错会让你看起来像一只真正的獾兽！",en:"Writing the name of these boots incorrectly will make you look like a real Badgerox!"};
descriptions["21730"]={cn:"蚀影斗篷的大姐，这件披风的第一个复制品是由同一个皮匠大师设计的。",en:"Big sister of the Apothecloakery, the first copy of this cape was designed by the same leather dealer."};
