descriptions["29471"]={cn:"这副肩甲上的磁力会将所有的敌人都吸引过来， 用来快速解决那些可悲的笨蛋非常实用。",en:"The magnetism in these epaulettes draws all your enemies to you at once. Very practical for putting an end to those miserable louts as quickly as possible."};
descriptions["29472"]={cn:"这副肩甲上的磁力会将所有的敌人都吸引过来， 用来快速解决那些可悲的笨蛋非常实用。",en:"The magnetism in these epaulettes draws all your enemies to you at once. Very practical for putting an end to those miserable louts as quickly as possible."};
descriptions["29473"]={cn:"塔特苏这名时间法师，是法律和正义的狂热捍卫者。每个人都喜欢他，认为他是个非常好的人，直到他与一名叫戈尔法布的恶魔缔结了契约。他在吉他方面有着非凡的技巧，但魔族给了他一个诅咒，使每个人都无法嘲笑他的恶作剧。就这样，塔特苏树立了非常非常多的敌人；很多人一直记得他是个顽皮的捣蛋鬼。\n幸运的是，他有几个朋友支持着他，并设法暂时解除了他的诅咒。他们将戈尔法布和他的同伙凯伊坦，放逐到远离十二世界的地方。\n接下来是我，你忠诚的仆人，不敢恣意完整讲述的冒险。故事的寓意在于正义是主观的，而且没有人喜欢塔特苏的歌。",en:"Tatsu the Xelor was a fervent defender of law and justice. Everyone liked him and thought he was very nice, that is until he made a pact with a demon called Gor\'fab. He developed exceptional skill at the guitar, but the Shushu came with a curse that prevented everyone from laughing at his practical jokes. Thus, Tatsu made many, many enemies. Many still remember him as a naughty troublemaker.\nLuckily for him, a few friends remained loyal and managed to lift he curse temporarily. They exiled Gor\'fab and his accomplice, Kaietan, far from the World of Twelve.\nWhat followed are adventures that I, your devoted servant, dare not tell in full without risk. But the moral of the story is that justice can be subjective, and no one likes Tatsu\'s songs."};
descriptions["29474"]={cn:"塔特苏这名时间法师，是法律和正义的狂热捍卫者。每个人都喜欢他，认为他是个非常好的人，直到他与一名叫戈尔法布的恶魔缔结了契约。他在吉他方面有着非凡的技巧，但魔族给了他一个诅咒，使每个人都无法嘲笑他的恶作剧。就这样，塔特苏树立了非常非常多的敌人；很多人一直记得他是个顽皮的捣蛋鬼。\n幸运的是，他有几个朋友支持着他，并设法暂时解除了他的诅咒。他们将戈尔法布和他的同伙凯伊坦，放逐到远离十二世界的地方。\n接下来是我，你忠诚的仆人，不敢恣意完整讲述的冒险。故事的寓意在于正义是主观的，而且没有人喜欢塔特苏的歌。",en:"Tatsu the Xelor was a fervent defender of law and justice. Everyone liked him and thought he was very nice, that is until he made a pact with a demon called Gor\'fab. He developed exceptional skill at the guitar, but the Shushu came with a curse that prevented everyone from laughing at his practical jokes. Thus, Tatsu made many, many enemies. Many still remember him as a naughty troublemaker.\nLuckily for him, a few friends remained loyal and managed to lift he curse temporarily. They exiled Gor\'fab and his accomplice, Kaietan, far from the World of Twelve.\nWhat followed are adventures that I, your devoted servant, dare not tell in full without risk. But the moral of the story is that justice can be subjective, and no one likes Tatsu\'s songs."};
descriptions["29475"]={cn:"这把斧头属于战争、暴力、黑暗和死亡之神；对，就是一个代表这么多象征的神。但我们说的不是兀枢，而是一个就是如此可怕的存在，他光是出现就足以让雪飞回落下的云层中。我想你可以称之为升雪而非降雪。",en:"This ax belonged to the god of war, violence, darkness and death. Yep, all that at once. Nope, we\'re not talking about Rushu. We\'re talking about an entity so terrible that his very presence is enough to send snow fleeing back into the clouds from which it fell. I guess you could call that snowflee instead of snowfall."};
descriptions["29476"]={cn:"这把斧头属于战争、暴力、黑暗和死亡之神；对，就是一个代表这么多象征的神。但我们说的不是兀枢，而是一个就是如此可怕的存在，他光是出现就足以让雪飞回落下的云层中。我想你可以称之为升雪而非降雪。",en:"This ax belonged to the god of war, violence, darkness and death. Yep, all that at once. Nope, we\'re not talking about Rushu. We\'re talking about an entity so terrible that his very presence is enough to send snow fleeing back into the clouds from which it fell. I guess you could call that snowflee instead of snowfall."};
descriptions["29477"]={cn:"沃土时代与上古时代相隔了许多年，只有很少的事物留存了下来。许多现实已经被时间所改变，曾经真实的故事变成了虚构和传说。但在这些冒险中，有一件是永恒而不变的：关于一名熊猫武僧挥舞着多啦笠帽的故事。",en:"The Dofus Era and the Wakfu Era are separated by many long years. A closer look shows that very little remains. Many realities have been transformed by time, and once-factual tales have become fiction and legend. But among all these adventures, one thing remains unchanging and eternal: the tale of a Pandawa wielding a Dora Lagoole."};
descriptions["29478"]={cn:"沃土时代与上古时代相隔了许多年，只有很少的事物留存了下来。许多现实已经被时间所改变，曾经真实的故事变成了虚构和传说。但在这些冒险中，有一件是永恒而不变的：关于一名熊猫武僧挥舞着多啦笠帽的故事。",en:"The Dofus Era and the Wakfu Era are separated by many long years. A closer look shows that very little remains. Many realities have been transformed by time, and once-factual tales have become fiction and legend. But among all these adventures, one thing remains unchanging and eternal: the tale of a Pandawa wielding a Dora Lagoole."};
descriptions["29479"]={cn:"据说这把铲子主要是用来打顽皮的孩子，由一名行为古怪的幸运猫制作。他非常友好，但有时会有一些看上去非常可疑的习惯，例如将他的仆人绑在他的散热器上。\n他不是一个伟大的战士，但他神秘的不可预测性仍然铭刻于人们的记忆中。传说中，他曾经独自一人被一群可怕的战士围住，最终在因伤口不支倒地前解决了了五名对手。",en:"They say that this shovel was mostly used to whack mischievous children. It was forged by an Ecaflip who behaved oddly. He was sometimes very friendly but had a few very questionable habits such as tying his servants to his radiator.\nHe wasn\'t a great warrior, but his mythic unpredictability has remained engraved in memory. Legend says that once, alone and circled by fearsome fighters, he took five opponents down with him before succumbing to his wounds."};
descriptions["29480"]={cn:"据说这把铲子主要是用来打顽皮的孩子，由一名行为古怪的幸运猫制作。他非常友好，但有时会有一些看上去非常可疑的习惯，例如将他的仆人绑在他的散热器上。\n他不是一个伟大的战士，但他神秘的不可预测性仍然铭刻于人们的记忆中。传说中，他曾经独自一人被一群可怕的战士围住，最终在因伤口不支倒地前解决了了五名对手。",en:"They say that this shovel was mostly used to whack mischievous children. It was forged by an Ecaflip who behaved oddly. He was sometimes very friendly but had a few very questionable habits such as tying his servants to his radiator.\nHe wasn\'t a great warrior, but his mythic unpredictability has remained engraved in memory. Legend says that once, alone and circled by fearsome fighters, he took five opponents down with him before succumbing to his wounds."};
descriptions["29481"]={cn:"这把弓是由阿维奥拉制作，他是一位痴迷于喱维萨派对的音乐大师。这把弓射出的箭会使目标跳舞，直到他们倒下为止。有些人会因此筋疲力尽而死，但如果目标喝了鸡尾酒，效果就会消失。",en:"This bow was forged by Aviola, a master musician obsessed with the parties in Bilbiza. The arrows it shoots make their targets dance until they drop. Some have died of exhaustion, but the effect wears off if the target drinks a cocktail."};
descriptions["29482"]={cn:"这把弓是由阿维奥拉制作，他是一位痴迷于喱维萨派对的音乐大师。这把弓射出的箭会使目标跳舞，直到他们倒下为止。有些人会因此筋疲力尽而死，但如果目标喝了鸡尾酒，效果就会消失。",en:"This bow was forged by Aviola, a master musician obsessed with the parties in Bilbiza. The arrows it shoots make their targets dance until they drop. Some have died of exhaustion, but the effect wears off if the target drinks a cocktail."};
descriptions["29483"]={cn:"这是一把传奇的槌子，由奥加罗马，有史以来最英勇的福狸战士所持有。她以粉碎敌人的膝盖而闻名，并且还是一位出色的画家，慰藉了许多冒险者的双眼。",en:"This mace has a legendary reputation. It was wielded by Augaroma, one of the most valiant warriors to ever live. She was a Lenald known for having broken the neals of all her enemies, and for being an accomplished illustrator who brought comfort to the eyes of many adventurers."};
descriptions["29484"]={cn:"这是一把传奇的槌子，由奥加罗马，有史以来最英勇的福狸战士所持有。她以粉碎敌人的膝盖而闻名，并且还是一位出色的画家，慰藉了许多冒险者的双眼。",en:"This mace has a legendary reputation. It was wielded by Augaroma, one of the most valiant warriors to ever live. She was a Lenald known for having broken the neals of all her enemies, and for being an accomplished illustrator who brought comfort to the eyes of many adventurers."};
descriptions["29485"]={cn:"受此权杖影响的人将获得深沉、平静和永恒的安眠（换句话说，死亡）。\n务必确保它始终指向正确的位置。",en:"Whoever suffers the effects of this scepter will know profound, peaceful and eternal rest (in other words, death).\nMake sure it\'s always pointed in the right direction."};
descriptions["29486"]={cn:"受此权杖影响的人将获得深沉、平静和永恒的安眠（换句话说，死亡）。\n务必确保它始终指向正确的位置。",en:"Whoever suffers the effects of this scepter will know profound, peaceful and eternal rest (in other words, death).\nMake sure it\'s always pointed in the right direction."};
descriptions["29487"]={cn:"一层厚厚的神秘面纱笼罩着现在十二世界中最神秘的生物之一，它们花了数年时间跨过月岛和械勒神域。\n有人说克莱芙是一位伟大的战士，参与了史诗般的竞赛，她既是举办人，也是参赛者。其他人说她是一位画家，画出的作品令人难以描述。 最后一个点，也是最令人惊讶的一点，是她只是一位主席，仅此而已。\n我们可以肯定的是，有时会听到一个短语在幸运猫中流传着：“我想要我的论坛标题”...",en:"A thick veil of mystery surrounds all that now remains of one of the most enigmatic creatures in the World of Twelve that spent years striding across Moon Island and Xelorium.\nSome say that Kraive was a great warrior who took part in epic tournaments, both organizing them and competing in them. Others say she was a painter who painted indescribable works of art. One final theory, and by far the most surprising, is that she was a mere chair, nothing more nothing less.\nAll that we know for sure is that we sometimes hear a phrase echoing through Ecaflipus: \"I want my forum title\"..."};
descriptions["29488"]={cn:"一层厚厚的神秘面纱笼罩着现在十二世界中最神秘的生物之一，它们花了数年时间跨过月岛和械勒神域。\n有人说克莱芙是一位伟大的战士，参与了史诗般的竞赛，她既是举办人，也是参赛者。其他人说她是一位画家，画出的作品令人难以描述。 最后一个点，也是最令人惊讶的一点，是她只是一位主席，仅此而已。\n我们可以肯定的是，有时会听到一个短语在幸运猫中流传着：“我想要我的论坛标题”...",en:"A thick veil of mystery surrounds all that now remains of one of the most enigmatic creatures in the World of Twelve that spent years striding across Moon Island and Xelorium.\nSome say that Kraive was a great warrior who took part in epic tournaments, both organizing them and competing in them. Others say she was a painter who painted indescribable works of art. One final theory, and by far the most surprising, is that she was a mere chair, nothing more nothing less.\nAll that we know for sure is that we sometimes hear a phrase echoing through Ecaflipus: \"I want my forum title\"..."};
